main event: Hundreds of small, circular and flat disc-shaped objects were observed in the sky over Eglin AFB, Florida on March 23, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were white in color from a distance and silvery when closer.
One group of hundreds of objects was rectangular in shape and appeared to slowly elongate and then return to a rectangular shape.
Another group of 30-50 objects was oval-shaped and slowly moving towards the observer.

A third group of hundreds of objects had a round center and two extended wing-like appendages, with the left wing pointed downward and the right wing pointed upward, and the entire formation appeared to be turning similar to a flight of birds.
The objects were observed for a total duration of around 60-70 seconds.
sighted object: hundreds of small, circular and flat disc-shaped objects
